                            <comment id="15038627" author="mitdesai" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2015 21:30:39 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Attached the patch that changes the behavior.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;It takes in a new argument. When pigmix is run, if it is initiated with the flag set, it will delete the output dir after each each run. If nothing is specified, it runs the same way it runs currently.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="15038648" author="rohini" created="Thu, 3 Dec 2015 21:40:49 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Can you change the default setting to not delete the output?&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
